{
  "texts": [
    "Over-fragmentation in Medical domain.",
    "Overfragmentation (spliting of domain words in more than one subword) in tokenization is a significant challenge in adapting large language models (LLMs) to the medical domain due to specialized terminology.",
    "Si et al. (2019) highlighted the limitations of traditional tokenization on the task of clinical concept extraction where they show models like BERT poorly toknize medical named entities.",
    "Nguyen et al. (2019) emphasized the impact of lexical segmentation on transformer-based models and suggested that not only using a dominspecific vocabulary helps but also a continual pretraining phase helps.",
    "Yuan et al. (2022) introduced BioBART and Labrak et al."
  ]
}